parameters:
\n<Dodon>Oh, you're on trash duty too, huh? I wonder where all these
monsters keep popping up from. There must be quite a few
caverns around here, maybe connected to somewhere else.

\n<Dodon>The ground's sunk that much, after all. Well, we're
surveying the terrain, so I doubt Lumare will collapse any
further than this, at least.

\n<Dodon>Oh, it's \n[1]. Slimeys have been flowing in from the
underground water cavern. Creatures coming from such a place
give me the creeps.

\n<Annie>I picked up something weird, so I'll give it to you. I can't
use this kind of stuff.

\n<Annie>Blunt weapons are the best! Smashing an orc's skull is just
so satisfying! You think so too, right \n[1]?

\n<Annie>You've got the image of a mage, but you're pretty versatile,
huh! Nice! Let's hurry up and crush those orcs so we can go
back and drink!

\n<Annie>What do you mean by 'partial'? Does it feel different
depending on which part you smash? You really get it

\n<Wanz>Ah! We've got competing requests! I'm going to defeat more
orcs than you, just watch! Huh? More orcs...?

\n<Wanz>Thud! Ahahaha! More orcs, you say Ahahahaha! So many So
many Uhehehehehe
\n<Wanz>Now that I think about it, it wasn't that funny.

\n<Louie>I don't think \n[1] would get hurt in a place like this,
but let's stay alert and do our best. By the way, what
should we eat when we get home today?

\n<\n[1]>Louie, you're getting careless. Thinking about food while
we're working.

\n<Louie>This is what you call being at ease. By the way, I wonder if
we can eat salami?

\n<Wanz>One, two-, three... Huh? How many did I defeat? I've lost
count.

\n<Wanz>Maybe it's okay to report a few extra? It's just 100G after
all.

\n<Wanz>Nihhi Then, I'll say a bit more About a hundred million
defeated. My arms remember.

\n<Wanz>Mm-, I forgot. It sucks to lose out! But cheating isn't good
either, right?

\n<Louie>Doing work that helps people like this feels good, doesn't
it? We've been doing nothing but studying and training all
this time, right?

\n<Louie>It's a dirty town, but becoming independent in the outside
world is quite an experience, isn't it?

\n<Louie>If I don't think that way, I can't stand that dirty bed.
It's hard, the futon is heavy, and despite being heavy, it's
not even warm.
